This HTML code includes all the necessary components and event listeners to create a dynamic chemical reaction visualization application. The application allows users to switch between different modes (Diels-Alder reaction, regioselectivity, stereospecificity, and HOMO/LUMO interactions), adjust controls (inverse, focus, reaction evolution, and ERG/EWG effect), and visualize the corresponding chemical reactions and molecular structures. The p5.js library is used to create the canvas and handle drawing and animation logic.

